
// JSON

// JSON is a light-weight data exchange format for storing and transporting data.
// JSON format is text only and it can easily be sent to and from a server.
// JSON is language independent.
// JSON consists of key/value pairs.
// JSON can store arrays, objects, strings, numbers, booleans and null values.

// JSON Example,
/*
{
    "name": "John",
    "age": 22,
    "city": "New York"
}
*/